      “Everybody that has been placed into temporary housing by the city’s program is going to lose their space tomorrow.”
              
              Tuesday morning, a group of houseless people who had been evicted from public parks and put up by the city at the Comfort Hotel in Dartmouth got some disturbing news: once again, they are being evicted. “We are a bit frantic this morning and quite upset,” says Rachelle Sauvé, site coordinator for P.A.D.S. Community Network, a group giving resources to those staying at Meagher Park—also known as People’s Park——on the corner of Dublin and Chebucto Streets in Halifax.…
      
